      <h2 id="what-is-lob" class="text-3xl font-semibold text-pink-400 mb-4">What is the Lob Shot in Pickleball?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg mb-6">
        The lob shot is an important strategy in pickleball that involves sending the ball high over your opponent's head, typically aiming to land it deep in their court. This high arc forces your opponent to retreat back to the baseline, which can disrupt their positioning and rhythm. While the lob may seem like a simple shot, it requires precise timing, proper placement, and a strong understanding of your opponent’s tendencies.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg mb-6">
        Unlike the fast-paced volleys or aggressive smashes, the lob relies on height and depth, forcing the opponent to move backwards, creating opportunities for a well-timed attack or even setting up a winning shot. The lob is especially useful when you’re facing opponents who dominate the net, giving you an opportunity to neutralize their aggressive positioning.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg mb-6">
        If you want to improve your pickleball game, learning how to execute a proper lob shot is essential. By mastering the lob, you can add an element of surprise and strategic depth to your play, giving you the advantage in many situations.
      </p>
